6. ENFORCEMENT AND REMEDIES

Unauthorized use, reproduction, distribution, or modification of the Software
constitutes:

  (a) Copyright infringement under 17 U.S.C. § 501, subject to statutory
      damages of up to $150,000 per work infringed (17 U.S.C. § 504(c));
  (b) A violation of the DMCA, 17 U.S.C. § 1203, subject to statutory
      damages of up to $25,000 per violation;
  (c) A violation of the Computer Fraud and Abuse Act, 18 U.S.C. § 1030,
      subject to criminal penalties and civil liability;
  (d) Misappropriation of trade secrets under the DTSA, 18 U.S.C. § 1836,
      and LUTSA, La. R.S. 51:1433, entitling the Owners to injunctive relief,
      actual damages, unjust enrichment, exemplary damages up to twice the
      amount of actual damages for willful misappropriation, and attorneys'
      fees;
  (e) A violation of the Louisiana Computer-Related Crime Law, La. R.S.
      14:73.5, subject to criminal fines up to $10,000 and imprisonment for
      up to five years.

The Owners reserve the right to pursue all available legal remedies, including
injunctive relief, compensatory damages, statutory damages, punitive damages,
disgorgement of profits, and recovery of attorneys' fees and costs.

